🔹 Observer Design Pattern

- defines one to many dependency between objects.
- one object (subject) changes state, all its dependents (observers) are notified and updated automatically
-example : news agency (subject) broadcasts news to different news channels (observers)

// the subject
class NewsAgency {

	private List<Channel> observers = new ArrayList<>();

	public void addObserver(Channel channel) {
		observers.add(channel);
	}

	public void setNews(String news) {
		for(Channel channel: observers) {
			channel.update(news);
		}
	}
}

// the observer interface
interface Channel {
	void update(String news);
}

class TVChannel implements Channel {
	public void update(String news) {
		sout("TV news :" + news);
	}
}

- when a change in one object requires changing others and can't say how many
- provides loose coupling
- java.util.EventListener in swing or Flow API (reactive)


